commit 3dac0ef92618049f00e2e390f75c90c0b14a0d22
Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Tue Nov 20 21:04:59 2018 -0800

    Timeout and error propagation for unbound buffers

    Summary:
    Update the transport context with a timeout setter/getter instead of
    passing it as argument to its createPair function. This way, the
    unbound buffers created from the transport context can reuse that same
    timeout as default.

    The waitRecv/waitSend functions on an unbound buffer now take an
    optional timeout argument. If the operation times out, it signals all
    pairs in the transport context that a timeout happened, and throws a
    more detailed exception itself. All pairs in the transport context
    need to be closed when this happens, as we don't know if unbound
    buffers will be around after the timeout bubbles up to the
    application.

    Reviewed By: manojkris

    Differential Revision: D13103991

    fbshipit-source-id: 3ca7dd445292ddb59e249ea16ba80b0550d18ac5
