commit 0202d1e3695e6376d081ee670de886fca6c8f2e6
Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 25 11:01:54 2018 -0700

    Fix overflow in transport

    Summary:
    Doing a broadcast with 512M elements failed with writev returning
    EINVAL (Invalid argument). It turns out that the offset and length
    fields in the 'Op' struct in gloo/transport/tcp/pair.cc were both
    declared as a regular int and when used with 512M floats (total size
    of 2GB) caused a 32-bit integer overflow. Subsequently, writev saw a
    negative length argument, and returned EINVAL.

    This change fixes that, as well as an overflow when setting the TCP
    send buffer. This was subject to the same problem because setsockopt
    takes an integer optval. It doesn't make sense to ask the kernel for a
    send buffer of size 2GB, so they are limited to max out at 32MB now.

    Reviewed By: manojkris

    Differential Revision: D8601859

    fbshipit-source-id: 0a1490887335412514d0035980216db8d109e6a8
