Author: Manoj Krishnan <manojk@fb.com>
Date:   Fri Feb 9 14:26:09 2018 -0800

    ReduceScatter CPU Implementation

    Summary:
    Implementation based on recursive halving (i.e vector halving and distance doubling algorithm)

    High-level Steps:
    1. Recursive halving binary block - vector halving and distance doubling algorithm

    2. In the largest binary block, each process with rank p exchanges data with p', where p' is the bit-reverse of p. The reason to do this exchange is as as follows: After recursive halving, reduce-scatter data is in incorrect order among the processes in largest binary block

    3. Finally resitribute the data based on user specified distribution (specified thru' recvElems parameter)

    Reviewed By: wesolwsk

