Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 5 15:12:43 2017 -0700

    Fix synchronization issue with cudaMemcpy

    Summary:
    Running two or more test processes in parallel would result in
    spurious test failures. Only the synchronous CUDA tests would fail.
    This was caused by the incorrect assumption that cudaMemcpy was
    synchronous w.r.t. the host process. Instead, cudaMemcpy is launched
    on the default stream (stream 0) of a device, and will be synchronous
    only w.r.t. kernels launched on blocking streams on the same device.
    The additional load on stream 0 caused by running multiple processes
    resulted in compute kernels launched on non-blocking streams (as part
    of the collective implementations) to run *before* the cudaMemcpy call
    on stream 0 would finish, causing them to see invalid data.

    This is fixed by adding explicit stream synchronization in
    CudaFixture::assignValues and banning use of cudaMemcpy and implicit
    synchronization in favor of cudaMemcpyAsync and explicit
    synchronization.

    Many thanks to slayton58 and lukeyeager for debugging.
    Closes https://github.com/facebookincubator/gloo/pull/97

    Differential Revision: D5988234

    Pulled By: pietern

