Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Tue Sep 5 13:54:56 2017 -0700

    Step 1 of phased migration of timeout to context

    Summary:
    The timeout "state" is currently associated with the device instance
    and carried over to pairs upon creating them. It requires the API user
    to call setTimeout on the device before creating new pairs. This is
    cumbersome when you need to clone a context because there is no
    natural way to carry over its timeout. This commit is phase 1 in a 2
    phase migration to store the timeout with the context instead of the
    device.

