commit 84c1c69f919ff7230fde57e3a14831f16f61f0c9
Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Thu Aug 31 13:12:33 2017 -0700

    Stop relying on bundled version of NCCL

    Summary:
    NCCL1 is deprecated in favor of NCCL2 and if anyone wants to still use
    it they can specify to do so via NCCL_ROOT_DIR.

    This change removes the NCCL submodule and makes use of NCCL a compile
    time option and constant. If USE_NCCL=ON, then all device side
    reductions are performed using NCCL. Otherwise, they are performed with
    a tree of CUDA reductions. Calls to cudaDeviceReduce or
    cudaDeviceBroadcast are handled based on the USE_NCCL constant.
    Closes https://github.com/facebookincubator/gloo/pull/80

    Reviewed By: wesolwsk

