commit 29f7ed256df4ccda672a059203e0e35a8fb0c4ad
Author: Pieter Noordhuis <pietern@fb.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 29 15:02:47 2017 -0700

    Include memory region sge on every receive work request

    Summary:
    In all uses of an ibverbs pair, it would first exchange memory
    regions for all buffers, before moving on to send/recv on those
    buffers. Receives for memory regions and RDMA receives were posted
    separately and because they were not interleaved this worked fine.

    When these receive operations were interleaved, I saw received memory
    regions equal to all NULs. Treating these two types of receives
    differently caused a mismatch between posted receives on the
    completion queue and the list with memory regions that the code
    expected to take writes. And because all inbound writes are one-sided,
    we never know whether we have to expect a memory region write or an
    RDMA write.

    This change merges the approaches so that we only deal with a single
    type of receive, that opportunistically includes a scatter/gather list
    with the memory address of a memory region. That way, if the remote
    side sends a memory region, it can be received, and if it performs an
    RDMA write, it will simply be ignored. To map receive work requests to
    memory regions, we keep track of the number of receive work requests
    posted and index into a fixed array of memory regions. This array can
    be fixed because we configure an upper bound to the number of pending
    read work requests (kRecvCompletionQueueCapacity).
    Closes https://github.com/facebookincubator/gloo/pull/77

